editorialDecl.p:
Named entities of the text (i.e. persons, places, work titles, dates) are annotated and
          linked to online resources including the Buddhist Digital Archives (BUDA;
          https://https://library.bdrc.io//), the Sakya Research Centre (SRC;
          https://sakyaresearch.org/) and the Resources for Kanjur & Tanjur Studies (rKTs;
          https://www.istb.univie.ac.at/kanjur). Non-canonical works are referred to by its Tohoku
          catalogue number (i.e. A catalogue of the Tohoku University collection of Tibetan works on
          Buddhism. Kanakura et al. (eds.). Sendai: Seminary of Indology, Tohoku University, 1953).
          Dates of persons are given according to the BUDA database.
